description:
&lt;p&gt;As part of the Trust’s procurement modernisation agenda, the procurement department will set its forward plan to achieve the vision as a best in class procurement function by 2020 – a journey of systems modernisation, review and revamp of processes and growth in the procurement knowledge and skills sector aimed at benefitting not only PAH, but the procurement sector in Essex and the wider East of England.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of these stated modernisations, the role of Category Specialists, with leadership guidance from the Procurement Manager, is a key part of the tactical shift from price and supply assurance, to the wider total cost of ownership and business partnering to transform procurement’s value proposition from merely supply assurance, to a function embedded with operational efficiency and optimised value management.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameSharon LoomesJob titleDeputy Head of ProcurementEmail addresssharon.loomes@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
